msgSnippet: Yes.  All of my real projects have used (or are using) JUnit and the last 4 or 5 have used HTTPUnit.  Here s a sample list: - Interface: L2i - Tumbleweed
messageBody:
Yes. All of my 'real' projects have used (or are using) JUnit and the
last 4 or 5 have used HTTPUnit. Here's a sample list:
- Interface: L2i
- Tumbleweed Communications: various projects
- Menlo Innovations: various projects
- ProQuest: HeritageQuestOnline
- University of Michigan Health System: OTIS 2 (Organ Transplantation
Information System rewrite project)
- My own paying gigs on the side

What is it you are after specifically?

You can also see http://c2.com/cgi-bin/wiki?WhoIsUsingJunit for a list
of JUnit users. For concrete examples that won't breach any contracts
of confidentiality see the tests in:
1. JUnit! (what a concept)
2. Jakarta Ant
3. etc.

=jason
